CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper July 1, 1939, pg. 14, reads: "Courier photographers snapped this gay group of Detroiters when they stopped in Pittsburgh enroute to Richmond for the N. A. A. C. P. annual convention."
TitMainTitle: Two women standing in front of bus with banner reading "On To Richmond, Detroit NAACP, Youth Councils and Senior Branch, Largest Branch in the USA"
